    1427 SIL
    Scalar Index List
    Main Index
    One logical record that contains a list of SIL numbers for each grid or scalar point. The list is in internal sort,
    therefore, internal number is implied by word position in the record. Definition of SIL numbers is as follows
    Let i = internal number, then SIL1 = 1, SILi+1=SILi + 6 if i = grid point =SILi + 1 if i = scalar point =SILi + 1 if i = Heat Transfer Problem Record 0 - HEADER Record 1 - SILREC Record 2 - TRAILER SIL Scalar Index List Word Name Type Description 1 NAME(2) CHAR4 Block name Word Name Type Description 1 SIL I Scalar Index List item Word 1 repeats until End of Record Word Name Type Description 1 WORD1 I = number of grid points + number of scalar points 2 WORD2 I = degrees of freedom in the g displacement set 3 WORD3 I = 0 4 WORD4 I = 0 5 WORD5 I = 0 6 WORD6 I = 0 Notes: 1.SIL numbers are integers.

    SLT Table of Static and Thermal Loads1430 Main Index The header record of the SLT contains a sorted list of all unique load set IDs contained on static load entries except the LOAD entry. The n logical records that follow the header record comprise all static load data belonging to each of the n load sets one logical record per load set. SLT is is undescribable because Record 2 is repeating and Record n+1 has a different format than Record 2. The (n+1)-th logical record contains all LOAD entries (if any).
